## CI enforcement

Two CI audits enforce this discipline. Both run on every PR + push to
`main` via `.github/workflows/audits.yml`:

- `scripts/audit-toolchain-currency.sh` — three checks bundled:
  1. Every rule/skill/subagent file's frontmatter `lastUpdated:` is at
     least as recent (date-only) as the file's git mtime. Catches
     "edited a file but forgot to bump the date stamp."
  2. Every rule/skill/subagent file has a row in
     `.cursor/TOOLCHAIN.md`. Catches "added a new file but forgot the
     index."
  3. Every TOOLCHAIN row's date matches the source file's frontmatter
     `lastUpdated:` exactly. Catches "bumped the file but forgot to
     regenerate the index."
- `scripts/audit-agent-docs-currency.sh` — blocks merge if a
  rule/skill/subagent file exists but isn't referenced on the
  cursor-workflows page (or the reverse). Internal-only artifacts that
  intentionally aren't on the page belong in
  `scripts/audit-baseline.json`
  `audit-agent-docs-currency.toleratedFiles`.

If `audit-toolchain-currency.sh` fails, the failure message includes the
exact fix command per row. The most common one-shot remediation is:

```bash
date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ                                # check today's UTC stamp
# edit your rule/skill/agent file's frontmatter lastUpdated to match
bash scripts/regenerate-toolchain.sh                       # rebuild TOOLCHAIN.md
bash scripts/audit-toolchain-currency.sh                   # confirm clean
```
